<section class="section" id="features">
  <p class="section-label">How it works</p>
  <h2 class="section-title">The Tiptap of Gantt charts</h2>
  <p class="section-desc">Frappe Gantt is the engine — rock-solid date math, drag handling, dependency resolution. Emboss wraps it in a design system, extension architecture, and glass-finished visual layer.</p>
  <div class="philosophy-grid">
    <div class="philosophy-card">
      <div class="philosophy-icon">&loz;</div>
      <h3>Everything is a Row</h3>
      <p>Phases, tasks, milestones, subtasks — one data model, one render pipeline. Extensions enrich rows. Renderers consume them.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="philosophy-card">
      <div class="philosophy-icon">&#9678;</div>
      <h3>Glass-finished bars</h3>
      <p>Track + fill + glass highlight + shadow. Progress markers, smart labels, drag handles. Every bar looks designed by hand.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="philosophy-card">
      <div class="philosophy-icon">&#10192;</div>
      <h3>Extensions, not forks</h3>
      <p>Today markers, tooltips, arrows, sidebars, milestones — all extensions. Register what you need. Override what you want.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="philosophy-card">
      <div class="philosophy-icon">&#9670;</div>
      <h3>Themes via CSS vars</h3>
      <p>Every visual value flows through custom properties. Light, dark, vivid — swap a class, change the feel. Build your own in 20 lines.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

